newsitem.title: UK: High prices subdue trade on UK meals/feeds market - Feb 13.
newsitem.headline: High prices subdue trade on UK meals/feeds market - Feb 13.

text.p: Gains of three to four stg a tonne in high protein soymeal prices kept most buyers out of the UK meals and feeds market on Thursday.
Prices rose sharply following the higher close in Chicago on Wednesday on the back of the USDA's supply and demand report and on a strong dollar.
"Buyers don't like high prices and will now only buy hand-to-mouth,' said one broker.
However, some trading was reported but tonnages were low.

Home produced wheat feed pellets fetched 90 stg for spot in south-east England while in the south-west port of Teignmouth 131 stg was paid for spot EU rapemeal and 212 stg for spot high protein soymeal.
